{{Infobox business park | name = Midtown Centre | image = | image_size = | caption = | location = [[Jacksonville, Florida|Jacksonville]], [[Florida]], [[United States]] | address = 3947 Boulevard Center Drive, Jacksonville, FL 32207 | coordinates = {{coord|30.300575|-81.619804}} | map_type = Florida | map_caption = Location within Florida | opening_date = 1957 | closing_date = | developer = Ira M. Koger | construction_cost = | manager = D Group Management NA | owner = D Group Equities | architect = | number_of_tenants = | number_of_workers = | size = 763,000 square feet | parking = | website = {{URL|midtowncentre.com}} | footnotes = }}
'''Midtown Centre''' is a [[business park]] located in the [[Jacksonville, Florida|Jacksonville]], [[Florida]] neighborhood of [[St. Nicholas (Jacksonville)|St. Nicholas]]. The site contains 31 buildings and was developed by Ira M. Koger. Opening in 1957 as the Koger Center, the facility is credited with being the first suburban office park.<ref name="Dunham-JonesWilliamson2011">{{cite book|author1=Ellen Dunham-Jones|author2=June Williamson|title=Retrofitting Suburbia, Updated Edition: Urban Design Solutions for Redesigning Suburbs|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1xH4b4pQzOkC&pg=PA206|accessdate=12 December 2012|date=23 March 2011|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=978-1-118-02767-7|pages=206–}}</ref> It is now (December 2012) owned by D Group Equities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.midtowncentre.com/pages/aboutus.aspx |title=About Midtown Centre Office Park |publisher=midtowncentre.com |date= |accessdate=2012-12-12}}</ref>
